        "instruction": "Fill in the blanks to complete the conditional statement based on the Introduction to Java Control Flow Essentials. Refer to the learning cards for clues.",
        "codeTemplate": "if (___) { System.out.println(\"Condition is true\"); } else { System.out.println(\"Condition is false\"); }",
        "options": [
          "condition",
          "true",
          "false",
          "expression"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": "condition",
        "explanation": "The blank should be filled with a valid condition that evaluates to true or false, which is essential in control flow."
      },
      {
        "instruction": "Complete the following code snippet using the correct control structure terminology learned in the Introduction to Java Control Flow Walkthrough.",
        "codeTemplate": "if (___) { System.out.println(\"You are correct!\"); } ___ { System.out.println(\"Try again.\"); }",
        "options": [
          "condition",
          "else",
          "if",
          "switch"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": "condition, else",
        "explanation": "The first blank requires a condition for the if statement, and the second blank must be filled with 'else' to complete the structure."
      }
    ]
  }
